snippet.textDisplay:
Honestly I used to be a cook in multiple restaurants and loved it . I used to be forced to watch Hell's Kitchen with an old girlfriend and it took quite a few episodes before I realized exactly what was going on.. and used to call him a strait up ASS that would get stabbed in most kitchens because you CANNOT YELL with that much sharp shit, boiling shit, and multiple heat sources around....
I FULLY ADMIT now that I was completely and utterly wrong about this man. I get that Hell's Kitchen is basically BOOT CAMP and they sign up for it , but more over I RESPECT THIS MAN for his WORK enough that I would let him yell at me till the cows come home if it were to make me even 1/8 of the chef he is.
Recently during this lockdown have been binging many of his shows and realized something else I didn't know .. He is the definition of a SELF MADE MAN... coming from the dish station to where he is NOW is ALL based on skill and brutal honesty with himself and others... MANY people think of me as an asshole ... I tend to be pretty brutally honest myself because I find everything else to be a waste of time.
Ramsey has EVERY RIGHT to be arrogant as hell.. but he really isn't , he is merely confident in what he does and KNOWS WHAT HE IS DOING.. Finding bosses and even just people with as much integrity , drive, and respect for the WORKERS is very very hard, and I wish more bosses were even an 1/8 as nurturing as Ramsey. As well as wish more MILLIONAIRES were 1/16 as generous and GIVE BACK to the communities and people that made them rich in the first place ..
THANK YOU CHEF , during this lockdown A LOT of depressions are going to set in and mine is no different and these videos and shows are helping me immensely. OH ... and cool video , sandwich looked crazy good.
